Name: Description
Graduation Rate by Economic Status: New York City public high school students who graduated as of June after four years of instruction.

Name: Source Notes
Graduation Rate by Economic Status: New York City Department of Education, Graduation Results (School Years 2004-05 to 2018-19); retrieved from https://infohub.nyced.org/reports-and-policies/citywide-information-and-data/graduation-results

Name: Notes
Graduation Rate by Economic Status: All data represent outcomes as of June after four years of instruction. In order to comply with FERPA regulations on public reporting of education outcomes, breakdowns where the number of students in the cohort is 5 or less are suppressed and maps and tables display "no data" or "0".
